    "revise": "You are the FIGURE REVISER (Opus) for \"The LLM Stack\". Chapter: content/01-foundations/07-autodiff-pytorch.md\nThe chapter's core intuitions: Reverse-mode autodiff propagates vector-Jacobian products (VJPs) backward through a recorded tape and never materializes the Jacobian, so ONE backward pass yields all N gradients regardless of parameter count.; The forward pass does two jobs at once: it builds the graph AND stashes the activations each op will need; backward then walks the graph in reverse topological order applying x-bar = y-bar^T J at every node.; Only leaf tensors accumulate .grad (through an AccumulateGrad node); intermediate-tensor gradients are discarded. When one tensor feeds multiple ops, its gradient contributions SUM at the leaf -- this is the same accumulation that gradient-accumulation training exploits.; Every op is routed through the dispatcher (autograd layer -> dispatch key -> ATen -> hardware kernel); that clean boundary is why torch.compile, vmap, and new backends plug in without touching user code.\n\nReview each of these figures (the ones this chapter just drew/edited):\n  autograd-graph-leaf-accumulate, tensor-storage-strides-views\n\nFor EACH: render and SEE it \u2014 `python3 scripts/preview_fig.py <NAME> --theme both` from /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook,\nthen view /tmp/figpreview/<NAME>.light.png and .dark.png. Judge strictly:\n  - Does it actually BUILD INTUITION for its concept (not just decorate)? Is it correct vs the chapter?\n  - Theme-safe (no hardcoded primary color; readable in BOTH light and dark)?\n  - Nothing clipped by the viewBox; no illegible overlaps; no tofu glyphs (ASCII only in the SVG)?\n  - Marker present in the chapter exactly once; figcaption has a bold lead + takeaway?\nIf a figure has ANY problem, FIX it: Edit /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook/figures/<NAME>.html (and re-render to confirm), or\nfix a missing/duplicate marker in the chapter. Re-verify after fixing.\n\nSet verdict per figure: good / fixed / still-broken / missing. `passed` = every figure good-or-fixed\nAND present. Return the structured object."
